.TH "__device_reset" 9 "__device_reset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__device_reset \- find reset controller associated with the device and perform reset
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __device_reset
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "bool optional "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device to be reset by the controller
.IP "optional" 12
whether it is optional to reset the device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Convenience wrapper for \fB__reset_control_get\fP and \fBreset_control_reset\fP.
This is useful for the common case of devices with single, dedicated reset
lines.
